      "date": "2013-10-11 08:31:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIt probably makes sense to cherry-pick the patches from the upstream kernel, so that the Author information stays the same. Also, the upstream commit hash should be in a Kernel-commit: tag so that it can be tracked more easily.\n\nUnfortunately, if there is a Signed-off-by: line in the commit message it will automatically add that person as a reviewer, which we probably don't want...  Maybe if they do not have Gerrit accounts, they won't get an email?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
